  2019,"10",/general-conference/2019/10/14christofferson,Elder D. Todd Christofferson,62,"We remember the words of James that inspired Joseph Smith to “ask of God” (James 1:5). Less familiar are the preceding verses:"
  2019,"10",/general-conference/2019/10/14christofferson,Elder D. Todd Christofferson,63,"“My brethren, count it all joy when ye fall into many afflictions;"
  2019,"10",/general-conference/2019/10/14christofferson,Elder D. Todd Christofferson,64,"“Knowing this, that the trying of your faith worketh patience."
  2019,"10",/general-conference/2019/10/14christofferson,Elder D. Todd Christofferson,65,"“But let patience have her perfect work, that ye may be perfect and entire, wanting nothing” (Joseph Smith Translation, James 1:2 [inJames 1:2, footnotea];James 1:3–4)."
  2019,"10",/general-conference/2019/10/14christofferson,Elder D. Todd Christofferson,66,"SeeMoses 1:39."
