  2019,"10",/general-conference/2019/10/41gong,Elder Gerrit W. Gong,59,"Generations can learn from each other, even as each generation learns for itself. The Christian writer Søren Kierkegaard intriguingly suggests, “Whatever the one generation may learn from the other, the genuinely humane no generation learns from the foregoing” (Fear and Trembling,trans. Vigilius Haufniensi [2018], 117)."
